---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const updated = 'May 2025';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — Aspect Builds & Maintenance Ltd"
  description="How Aspect Builds & Maintenance Ltd collects, uses and protects your personal data."
>
  <section class="doc-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="rule--accent"></span>
      <span class="t-label" style="color:var(--accent)">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="doc-hero__heading">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="doc-hero__meta">Aspect Builds & Maintenance Ltd &mdash; Last updated {updated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-body">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="doc-content">

        <div class="doc-intro">
          <p>Aspect Builds & Maintenance Ltd ("<strong>we</strong>", "<strong>us</strong>", "<strong>our</strong>") is committed to protecting your personal data. This policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and your rights under the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018.</p>
          <p>Our registered business address is in Bath, Somerset, England. If you have any questions about this policy, contact us at <a href="mailto:hello@aspectbuilds.co.uk">hello@aspectbuilds.co.uk</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 class="doc-section__heading">1. What Data We Collect</h2>
          <p>When you submit an enquiry through our website contact form, we collect:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Full name</li>
            <li>Phone number</li>
            <li>Email address</li>
            <li>Project location (area)</li>
            <li>Service type and estimated investment range</li>
            <li>Planning/drawings status</li>
            <li>Project brief and any other details you include</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We also collect standard technical data automatically when you visit the website, including your IP address, browser type, pages visited, and time of visit. This is collected via server logs and any analytics tools we operate.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 class="doc-section__heading">2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
          <p>We use the information you provide to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Respond to your project enquiry and assess whether we can assist</li>
            <li>Arrange site appraisals, consultations, or quotations</li>
            <li>Communicate with you during the course of any works</li>
            <li>Meet our legal and contractual obligations</li>
          </ul>
          <p>We do not use your data for unsolicited marketing. We will not send you promotional emails unless you have explicitly agreed to receive them.</p>
          <p><strong>Lawful basis:</strong> We process your data on the basis of <em>legitimate interests</em> (responding to your enquiry) and, where a contract is formed, <em>performance of a contract</em>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 class="doc-section__heading">3. How We Store & Protect Your Data</h2>
          <p>Enquiry data submitted via our contact form is processed and stored by <strong>Netlify</strong> (our hosting and form provider). Netlify is GDPR-compliant and processes data within the European Economic Area or under appropriate safeguards. You can review Netlify's privacy policy at <a href="https://www.netlify.com/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">netlify.com/privacy</a>.</p>
          <p>We retain enquiry data for a maximum of <strong>3 years</strong> from the date of submission, after which it is securely deleted. Data relating to active contracts is retained for <strong>7 years</strong> in line with HMRC requirements.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 class="doc-section__heading">4. Who We Share Your Data With</h2>
          <p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data. We may share it with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Netlify</strong> — our form processing and hosting provider</li>
            <li><strong>Our team members</strong> who need access to respond to or manage your enquiry</li>
            <li><strong>Professional advisers</strong> (e.g. accountants, solicitors) where legally required</li>
            <li><strong>Regulatory authorities</strong> if required by law</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 class="doc-section__heading">5. Cookies</h2>
          <p>Our website may use essential cookies to ensure it functions correctly. We do not currently use third-party tracking or advertising cookies. If this changes, we will update this policy and, where required, obtain your consent.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 class="doc-section__heading">6. Your Rights</h2>
          <p>Under UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Access</strong> — request a copy of the personal data we hold about you</li>
            <li><strong>Rectification</strong> — ask us to correct inaccurate data</li>
            <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — ask us to delete your data where there is no lawful reason to retain it</li>
            <li><strong>Restriction</strong> — ask us to restrict how we process your data</li>
            <li><strong>Objection</strong> — object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
            <li><strong>Portability</strong> — receive your data in a structured, machine-readable format</li>
          </ul>
          <p>To exercise any of these rights, email us at <a href="mailto:hello@aspectbuilds.co.uk">hello@aspectbuilds.co.uk</a>. We will respond within 30 days. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the <strong>Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</strong> at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 class="doc-section__heading">7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>We may update this policy from time to time. The date at the top of this page reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of the website after any change constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .doc-hero {
    background: var(--navy);
    padding: calc(var(--section-pad) * 0.8) 0 var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .doc-hero__heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 5rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #fff;
    margin: var(--space-s) 0 var(--space-m);
  }

  .doc-hero__meta {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .doc-body {
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .doc-content {
    max-width: 72ch;
  }

  .doc-intro {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-m);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--stone);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .doc-intro p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--concrete);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .doc-section {
    padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--stone);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-m);
  }

  .doc-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .doc-section__heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.2rem, 2vw, 1.6rem);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--chalk);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .doc-section p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--concrete);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .doc-section ul {
    padding-left: 0;
    margin: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .doc-section ul li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--concrete);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .doc-section ul li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .doc-section a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  .doc-section a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-dim);
  }
</style>
